<p></p>.<p>Dryness of the eyes can be a normal response to weather 
or medications. Dryness of the eyes can also result from temporary or chronic 
health conditions. The tears of the of eye come from the tear gland, called the 
lacrimal gland, which is located above the outer eye. Tears are composed of 
water, oil, and antibodies. The moisture from tears on the front of the eye, the 
<a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/eye_diseases_pictures_slideshow/article.htm" rel="slide" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">cornea</a>, is important to avoid damage of the cornea.</p>.<p class="credits">REFERENCE:<br><br>Kasper, D.L., et al., eds. <i>Harrison's Principles of Internal Medicine, 19th Ed</i>. United States: McGraw-Hill Education, 2015.</p>